    {
        "header": "3Methodology",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.08063/2606.08063v1/x3.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:Schematic of the dual-reward mechanism used in the reinforcement learning stage. (A)Pixel-Level Structural Reward:Computes the SSIM index by comparing local patches (luminance, contrast, structure) between the recovered image𝐈r\\mathbf{I}_{r}and the ground-truth clean image𝐈o\\mathbf{I}_{o}. (B)Semantic Consistency Reward:Utilizes a frozen TinyCLIP(Wuet al.,2023)model to extract image embeddings. The reward is derived from the cosine similarity between the embeddings of𝐈r\\mathbf{I}_{r}and𝐈o\\mathbf{I}_{o}, encouraging semantic alignment in the vision-language feature space.",
                "position": 514
            }
        ]
    },
